# Component and Icon Usage Guidelines

## Spring UI Components
- **Always use components from the `components/spring-ui` folder** when possible - this is our Spring Design System
- **Import from the correct path**: `@/components/spring-ui/[component-name]`
- Examples:
  - Use `<Button>` from [src/components/spring-ui/button.tsx](mdc:src/components/spring-ui/button.tsx) instead of HTML `<button>`
  - Use `<Input>` from [src/components/spring-ui/input.tsx](mdc:src/components/spring-ui/input.tsx) instead of HTML `<input>`
  - Use `<IconButton>` from [src/components/spring-ui/icon-button.tsx](mdc:src/components/spring-ui/icon-button.tsx) for buttons with icons
  - Use `<SegmentedControl>` from [src/components/spring-ui/segmented-control.tsx](mdc:src/components/spring-ui/segmented-control.tsx) for tab-like controls

### Available Spring UI Components
Key components in our design system:
- **Inputs**: `Button`, `IconButton`, `Input`, `Textarea`, `Select`, `Checkbox`, `Switch`, `Radio`
- **Layout**: `Modal`, `Popover`, `Dropdown Menu`, `Table`, `Row`, `Tab Bar`
- **Display**: `Badge`, `Tag`, `Avatar`, `Icon`, `Tooltip`
- **Complex**: `Autocomplete`, `Segmented Control`, `Split Button`, `Accordion`, `Slider`

## Designer Layout Components
- **Layout components** are located in `@/components/designer/layout/`
- **Section components** are located in `@/components/designer/sections/`
- Examples:
  - `Navbar`, `LeftSidebar`, `Canvas` from [src/components/designer/layout/](mdc:src/components/designer/layout)
  - `CMSSection`, `AppsSection` from [src/components/designer/sections/](mdc:src/components/designer/sections)

## Icon Usage
- **Always import icons from [src/icons](mdc:src/icons)** - never use third-party icon libraries if equivalent icons exist
- **Standard import pattern**: `import { IconName } from '@/icons'`
- **Default styling**: Icons should use `--text-secondary` color from our theme system:
  ```tsx
  // ✅ Correct usage
  <SomeIcon className="text-[var(--text-secondary)]" size={16} />
  
  // ✅ With additional styles
  <SomeIcon className="text-[var(--text-secondary)] mr-1.5" size={16} />
  
  // ❌ Avoid hardcoded colors
  <SomeIcon className="text-gray-500" size={16} />
  ```

### Icon Sizing Standards
- **Default size**: `16px` for most icons
  ```tsx
  // ✅ Standard usage
  <SomeIcon size={16} />
  
  // ❌ Avoid non-standard sizes
  <SomeIcon size={14} />
  ```
- **Size exceptions based on naming**:
  - Icons with "24" in name → use `size={24}` (e.g., `ToolbarHelp24Icon`)
  - Icons with "Capability" in name → use `size={24}`
  - Icons with "64" in name → use `size={64}` (e.g., `AddPanelButton64Icon`)

### Icon Naming Conventions
- **Standard icons**: Often include "Default" (e.g., `PageDefaultIcon`, `CheckDefaultIcon`)
- **Directional icons**: Include direction and size (e.g., `ChevronSmallDownIcon`, `ArrowUpRightIcon`)
- **Search tip**: Use regex search to find icons when uncertain about naming

## Component Styling Best Practices
- **Use built-in variants**: Leverage component props like `variant="ghost"`, `size="comfortable"`
- **Minimize custom classes**: Only add custom `className` when absolutely necessary
- **Follow established patterns**: Reference existing components for styling consistency
- **Use theme variables**: Apply colors via CSS variables from our theme system

### Button Examples
```tsx
// ✅ Correct - using variants
<Button variant="primary" size="comfortable">Primary Action</Button>
<Button variant="ghost" size="compact">Secondary</Button>

// ✅ With icons
<IconButton variant="ghost" size="icon">
  <SettingsIcon size={16} />
</IconButton>

// ❌ Avoid excessive custom styling
<Button className="bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-600 px-4 py-2">Custom Button</Button>
```

## Layout Pattern Guidelines
- **Consistent spacing**: Follow existing spacing patterns from components
- **Responsive design**: Maintain responsiveness across device sizes
- **Reference layouts**: Use patterns from [src/components/designer/layout/Canvas.tsx](mdc:src/components/designer/layout/Canvas.tsx) and similar files

## State Management
- **Component state**: Use React hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, etc.) for local component state
- **Global state**: Follow existing patterns from [src/context](mdc:src/context) for app-wide state
- **Form state**: Use controlled components with Spring UI form elements

## Import Organization
Keep imports organized and use correct paths:
```tsx
// ✅ Correct import structure
import { Button, IconButton } from '@/components/spring-ui/button'
import { Input } from '@/components/spring-ui/input'
import { SettingsIcon, ChevronDownIcon } from '@/icons'
import { SomeUtility } from '@/lib/utils'

// ✅ Designer components
import { Navbar } from '@/components/designer/layout/Navbar'
import { CMSSection } from '@/components/designer/sections/CMSSection'
```
